  "text": "Similar to what was reported by Coulman [CITATION_1] , AC Knowles produced slightly less than or was not different from Paddock, except during 2007, when Paddock had 70% more production than AC Knowles from initial spring growth (Table   4 ). The poorer performance of the hybrid bromegrass cultivars has also been seen in other climates with higher precipitation than that found on the Canadian Great Plains area, where these cultivars were developed (B. Coulman, personal observation).",
